Social Skills

With a career spanning over 23 years in software engineering and cloud architecture, he has developed strong interpersonal skills, essential for leading technical teams and collaborating with stakeholders in complex environments. He is communicative, objective, and skilled at translating technical challenges into strategic business solutions. His experience in global projects has enhanced his cultural adaptability and negotiation skills, always striving for excellence in delivery.

Personal Summary

A certified professional with over 70 technical certifications and a solid career in software engineering, DevOps, and cloud architecture. With more than two decades of experience, he has worked on strategic projects for major players in the financial and corporate sectors. His approach is based on innovation, efficiency, and continuous improvement, ensuring robust, scalable solutions aligned with industry best practices. He has expertise in multi-cloud environments, automation, digital security, and complex process modeling.

Organization Skills

Throughout his career, he has managed highly complex projects and globally distributed teams, requiring a high level of organization and strategic planning. He has strong expertise in agile methodologies (Scrum, Kanban, SAFe) and governance frameworks, ensuring efficiency in execution and delivery of technological products. His ability to manage time, prioritize tasks, and optimize processes allows him to work with high productivity while maintaining quality and scalability in delivered solutions.
